description.narrative:
"The aim of the project is to strengthen the capacities of Ukrainian, Georgian and Moldovan institutions and civil servants’ in the field of European integration management as well as increase the understanding of EU institutions about how to efficiently support Ukraine, Georgia and Moldova in the implementation of their Association Agreements with the EU. 
The project will
-	provide technical assistance and consultations of Lithuanian experts to Ukraine, Georgia and Moldova on European integration management (horizontal and sectoral issues of the implementation of Association Agreements, including DCFTA);
-	strengthen the analytical capacities and training (pedagogical) skills of European integration affairs‘ coordinators, sectoral experts and lawyers working in the public service in Ukraine, Georgia and Moldova;
-	systematize the best practice of European policy/European affairs coordination and to use it for more successful implementation of the Association Agreements with the EU."
